2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a technique to improve the channel estimation accuracy in multi-cellular massive MIMO systems, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with the problem of interference between users in a multi-cellular massive MIMO system, which can be seen as a social network problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of massive MIMO networks, which can be relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computational Complexity): The paper may involve some computational complexity in implementing the proposed blind equalization technique.
